{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/how-to-rustup","webpackCompilationHash":"ebd24d786d7b523a53b9","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"b43aeea9-9eb0-5908-9029-1c0aea8a579c","html":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#intro\">Intro</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#the-book\">The Book</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#rustlings\">Rustlings</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#whats-next\">What’s next</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/f7820/stock-photo.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/77824/stock-photo.webp 240w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/e7b60/stock-photo.webp 480w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/64043/stock-photo.webp 960w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/6ce15/stock-photo.webp 1440w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/f07e4/stock-photo.webp 1920w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/a3e00/stock-photo.webp 5000w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/24e5f/stock-photo.jpg 240w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/fe4bd/stock-photo.jpg 480w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/dff20/stock-photo.jpg 960w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/75e15/stock-photo.jpg 1440w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/32ee3/stock-photo.jpg 1920w,\n/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/f7820/stock-photo.jpg 5000w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/4e33feda8e66f912b0310c7458ef2bde/dff20/stock-photo.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Rusty lock\"\n          title=\"Rusty lock\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"intro\"><a href=\"#intro\" aria-label=\"intro permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intro</h2>\n<p>Before launching <a href=\"https://t.me/rustarmenia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Rust Community Armenia</a>, I decided to write a short article giving the reader a clear path to becoming a <a href=\"https://www.rustaceans.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">rustacean</a>.</p>\n<p>Instead of talking about killer features of the language, I will show you that whether you’re searching for a good book or a good set of exercises to get used to writing rust code rustaceans got you covered and its easier to learn the language than you could imagine.</p>\n<p>So let’s go ahead and review some nice things out there!</p>\n<h2 id=\"the-book\"><a href=\"#the-book\" aria-label=\"the book permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Book</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The Rust Book</a> is where your journey starts!</p>\n<p>What I mostly like about it is that its free from formal definitions and all topics are explained in the simplest possible way usually combined with real-world examples which clearly answers the most popular question every programmer asks after studying a tough topic - Why the hell I would use that? (I was asking this when reading about lifetimes :) </p>\n<p>After going through 20 chapters of the book you will get familiar with the most thought-provoking concepts of the language and even build a <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch20-00-final-project-a-web-server.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">multithreaded web server</a> at the end. For me, getting such a low-level control over connection streams and threading was an amazing and challenging experience, cause all such things are mostly done internally in Node.</p>\n<h2 id=\"rustlings\"><a href=\"#rustlings\" aria-label=\"rustlings permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rustlings</h2>\n<p>So here we are you’ve read the book and ready to move on.</p>\n<p>If you think you fully got the ownership and lifetime rules don’t worry there’s still a lot of work to do. And here’s where <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rustlings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">rustlings</a> comes to help. It’s a tool containing various helpful exercises to get you used to writing rust and reading others code which can seem awful at first IMHO.</p>\n<p>I personally recommend working on exercises after reading the book as a review process, because each chapter contains links to the related topic from the book so you can come back and strengthen your skills in a such way. </p>\n<p><em>Below is a bash code snippet to install and run rustlings on Linux/macOS.</em></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">export</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">DIR</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/path/to/download <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">curl</span> -L https://git.io/rustlings <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">bash</span> -s <span class=\"token variable\">$DIR</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$DIR</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\nrustlings <span class=\"token function\">watch</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Additionally, you may also use <a href=\"https://codesignal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CodeSignal</a> as part of your exercise routine. After doing some research I’ve found it to be one of the few platforms to fully support rust (HackerRank does also, but I’ve seen some tasks in which the language is not available).</p>\n<h2 id=\"whats-next\"><a href=\"#whats-next\" aria-label=\"whats next permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What’s next</h2>\n<p>Hooray! What a road it’s been. If I’m assuming right you went through everything mentioned above. Skilled and ready to hack, huh? Now it’s the right time to carefully study the <a href=\"https://www.rust-lang.org/what\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">use cases</a> of rust. As a web dev at heart, I chose to go with WebAssembly.</p>\n<p>By the time of writing Rust is not in <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rustlang/status/1294024734804508679\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">good shape</a> in terms of job availability but don’t worry, it’s all good! A lot of companies start using it so I’m sure you will find your place as well. So keep hacking! And remember <a href=\"\">#DontPlayJobSafe</a> - that’s the key and always will be!</p>\n<p>So far, this is it. These resources should be a good getting started point. For the next part, you may expect my thoughts about WebAssembly or my vision for Rust Community Armenia. Let’s see what happens.</p>\n<p>Best of luck and thank you!</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: <em>This article is written from the JS dev perspective who’s passionate about rust. You may not agree with some of the advice given, feel free to propose yours in the community <a href=\"https://t.me/rustarmenia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">chat</a>.</em></p>","fields":{"slug":"/how-to-rustup","tagSlugs":["/tag/rust/","/tag/cs/","/tag/review/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-08-16T15:35:00.121Z","description":"My way of becoming Rustacean","tags":["Rust","CS","Review"],"title":"How to get started with Rust?","socialImage":"/media/how-to-rustup.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/how-to-rustup"}}}